Create a virtual Environement somewhere outside this project filter
-     python -m venv ./

Activate the virtual Environment
-    just try to add a new powershell, visual studio will automatically activate the venv, you will see vs code run a command on the first line of the terminal like this `& "C:/Users/Mubarak Salley/Documents/Envs/py_tenacity_env/Scripts/Activate.ps1"`


Install Required Modules
-     pip install selenium
-     pip install jupyter  # This will make python interactive, not required

Type Ctrl+Shift+P , type "python intepreter" select your venv/script/python.exe

Download Firefox Geckodriver [This is for windows]
-     wget https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases/download/v0.32.2/geckodriver-v0.32.2-win32.zip -O ./mozillaGeckodriver.zip
-     tar -xf mozillaGeckodriver.zip

Copy the extract mozillaGeckodriver to the automation folder




